article.headline: North Texas 72, Denver 70
article.story: DENTON, Texas (AP) -- Isaac Hines scored 16 points off the bench to lead North Texas past Denver 72-70 on Monday night. Denver's DeShawn Walker had a chance to force overtime with a second left, but his jumper rimmed out. The loss spoiled Yemi Nicholson's big night. Nicholson had 28 points and 16 rebounds, including a dunk with 32 seconds left that brought Denver within two points. Kendrick Davis added 15 points for North Texas (10-7, 3-1 Sunbelt). The Mean Green were outrebounded 48-36, but forced 17 turnovers while committing only seven. Walker had 17 points and Steve Wetrich added 12 for Denver (10-5, 3-1).
